The following are [[List of international rankings|international rankings]] of [[Croatia]].
==General== * [[United Nations]]: [[List of countries by Human Development Index|Human Development Index]] [http://hdrstats.undp.org/en/countries/profiles/HRV.html 2010], ranked Croatia as [http://hdrstats.undp.org/en/countries/profiles/HRV.html 51st] out of 169 countries. In all, 194 countries were listed, but 25 were not ranked. Croatia is in the top third of nations labeled as having "high human development", which starts with the 43rd country. The top 42 nations in the index are labeled as having "very high human development". Human Development is quantified using such factors as longevity, education, and income. [http://hdr.undp.org/en/media/HDR_2010_EN_Table1_reprint.pdf Human Development Index and its components]
==Economic== * [[The Wall Street Journal]] and the [[Heritage Foundation]]: [[Index of Economic Freedom]] publish an annual [http://www.heritage.org/Index/ Index of Economic Freedom]. In 2011, they listed Croatia as having the [http://www.heritage.org/Index/Country/Croatia 82nd freest economy] among 179 countries in the world.
==Political== * [[Transparency International]] publishes an annual [[Corruption Perceptions Index]].<ref>http://www.transparency.org/policy_research/surveys_indices/cpi</ref> In [http://www.transparency.org/policy_research/surveys_indices/cpi/2010/results 2010], Croatia ranked 62nd out of 178 countries. The CPI measures the degree to which public sector corruption is perceived to exist in 178 countries around the world. The 2010 results are drawn from 13 surveys and assessments published between January 2009 and September 2010.[http://www.transparency.org/policy_research/surveys_indices/cpi/2010/in_detail CPI 2010] *[http://en.rsf.org/ Reporters Without Borders] publishes a Press Freedom Index. In [http://en.rsf.org/spip.php?page=classement&id_rubrique=1034 2010], Croatia tied for 62nd out of 178 countries, up from 78th in [https://web.archive.org/web/20150930230930/http://en.rsf.org/press-freedom-index-2009%2C1001.html 2009]. *The 2014 [[Global Peace Index]] ranked Croatia 26th out of 162 countries.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.visionofhumanity.org/sites/default/files/2014%20Global%20Peace%20Index%20REPORT.pdf |title=2014 Global Peace Index Report |format=PDF |publisher=[[Institute for Economics and Peace]] |date=June 2014 |accessdate=7 May 2015 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150221185512/http://www.visionofhumanity.org/sites/default/files/2014%20Global%20Peace%20Index%20REPORT.pdf |archivedate=21 February 2015 |df= }}</ref>
